    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public abstract boolean initialize()
        Initializes this data store prior to numeric function execution.

        Implementations of this method should perform any loading and/or processing required to make its data available to the functions being executed by the model.

        Note: This method will be called on each data store just before functions are executed.

        Returns:
        true if the initialization is successful; false if execution should be aborted.
        See Also:
        dispose(), AbstractNumericFunction, AbstractNumericsModel.executeUserDefinedFunctions()

      • dispose

        public abstract void dispose()
        Unloads and disposes of all unnecessary resources after numeric function execution.

        Implementations of this method should close all file handles and discard all transient data.

        Note: This method will be called on each data store just after functions are executed.

        See Also:
        initialize(), AbstractNumericFunction, AbstractNumericsModel.executeUserDefinedFunctions()

      • getValue

        public abstract java.lang.Object getValue​(java.lang.String key)
        Retrieves the value in this data store corresponding to the given key.

        Implementations of this method are free to return any appropriate data type for the given key.

        Parameters:
        key - a String containing the key to retrieving a data value
        Returns:
        an Object reference to the value corresponding to the given key.

      • complete

        public boolean complete​(InsertionSource insertSource)
        Description copied from class: AbstractComponent
        This method uses an InsertionSource object to completely control the insertion of this component. A valid implementation of this method must handle adding the component to the target model, initializing the component, and adding an appropriate undo-able edit to the source's CompoundEdit.

        When this method is called, this component has not been added to the model available from InsertionSource.getModel(). Refer to the source code documentation for InsertionSource for more information on this process.

        Note: Components that implement this method should not implement AbstractComponent.complete() as it will not be called if this method returns true.

        Overrides:
        complete in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:
        insertSource - the InsertionSource that should be used to guide the component insertion process.
        Returns:
        true if this component supports component initialization via an InsertionSource object; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        InsertionSource.componentAdded(AbstractComponent, boolean), InsertionSource.getEdit(), InsertionSource.getModel()

      • setNameConstrained

        public void setNameConstrained​(java.lang.String val_)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSharedValue
        Sets the name of this value. Names must be non-null, non-empty, and match the regular expression stored in AbstractSharedValue.NAME_REGEX_STANDARD. No two values falling under the umbrella of AbstractNumericsModel.CAT_SHARED_VALUE may have the same name. The legacy naming convention is suppored through AbstractSharedValue.NAME_REGEX_LEGACY for models that use it.
        Overrides:
        setNameConstrained in class AbstractSharedValue
